    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect eNB configuration indexing in RCconfig_S1 function\n\n### Summary\nThe RCconfig_S1 function was not properly using the passed eNB index parameter, causing it to configure the wrong eNB when multiple instances were present. This led to S1 setup failures and incorrect MME registration.\n\nThis fix ensures the function directly uses the provided index instead of looping through all eNB configurations.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/ENB_APP/enb_config.c`: Modified RCconfig_S1 to use direct indexing\n- `openair2/ENB_APP/enb_config.c`: Added active eNB list verification\n- `openair2/ENB_APP/enb_config.c`: Removed unnecessary nested loops\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen running multiple eNB instances with different configurations, the S1AP registration would sometimes use parameters from the wrong eNB instance, causing MME connection failures. The issue was more prevalent when the active eNB list order didn't match the configuration file order.\n\nTo reproduce:\n1. Configure multiple eNB instances with different MME addresses\n2. Start the eNB application\n3. Observe that some eNBs fail to register with their designated MMEs\n4. Check S1AP logs to see mismatched configuration parameters being used\n\n"
}